Tom Perez has been confirmed as Secretary of Labor. President Obama welcomes his confirmation and highlights Perez's dedication to helping hardworking families and keeping the American dream within reach. Perez's role will involve growing the economy, supporting job creation, ensuring workers have the necessary skills, and promoting safe workplaces and economic opportunities for all. The President expresses gratitude to the Senate for moving forward with the confirmation process for Perez and other nominees who have experienced delays.